<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<section xml:id="excel-5-8-minimization">
  <title>Excel Exploration: Minimization Criteria</title>

  <exercises xml:id="exercises5-8-excel" hidden-label="yes">
    <title>Exploration Tasks</title>

    <p>This activity compares minimization criteria for choosing a single-value predictor <m>m</m> for heights.</p>

    <exercise xml:id="excel5-8-a" label="E5.8.a"><title>Compute SAE from Mean</title><statement><p>(a) Compute SAE using mean as predictor.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="excel5-8-b" label="E5.8.b"><title>Compute SAE(m) in Spreadsheet</title><statement><p>(b) Fill formulas in <c>Heights.xls</c> and verify SAE at sample mean.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="excel5-8-c" label="E5.8.c"><title>Graph SAE(m)</title><statement><p>(c) Graph SAE vs m, sketch shape, and describe its form.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="excel5-8-d" label="E5.8.d"><title>Find Minimizer of SAE</title><statement><p>(d) Determine value(s) of m minimizing SAE and report minimum SAE.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="excel5-8-e" label="E5.8.e"><title>Connect to Median</title><statement><p>(e) Relate minimizing m to ordered data and familiar location statistics.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="excel5-8-f" label="E5.8.f"><title>Modify Middle Value</title><statement><p>(f) Change one middle value and reassess minimizer uniqueness.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="excel5-8-g" label="E5.8.g"><title>Modify Extreme Value</title><statement><p>(g) Change largest value and compare effect on SAE minimizer.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="excel5-8-h" label="E5.8.h"><title>General Conjecture</title><statement><p>(h) Conjecture rule for minimizing SAE from generic data.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="excel5-8-i" label="E5.8.i"><title>MAE Criterion</title><statement><p>(i) Compare MAE(m) and SAE(m): shape and minimizer.</p></statement><response/></exercise>

    <p><alert>Discussion:</alert> SAE is piecewise linear and minimized by a median value (or median interval for even n).</p>

    <exercise xml:id="excel5-8-j" label="E5.8.j"><title>Least-Squares Minimizer Recall</title><statement><p>(j) Report m that minimizes SSE for these heights.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="excel5-8-k" label="E5.8.k"><title>Graph SSE(m)</title><statement><p>(k) Graph SSE vs m, describe shape, and identify minimizer.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="excel5-8-l" label="E5.8.l"><title>Outlier Sensitivity Comparison</title><statement><p>(l) Create extreme outlier and compare effects on SSE and SAE minimizers.</p></statement><response/></exercise>

    <assemblage>
      <title>Discussion</title>
      <p>Least squares has computational and uniqueness advantages but is less resistant to outliers than absolute-error criteria.</p>
    </assemblage>
  </exercises>
</section>
